1. Discord Rich Presence (RPC)
Effort: 🟢 Very Low (30 mins) Why: It is free marketing. When your users listen to music, their Discord status will show "Listening to [Song Name] on SunoSync". This drives curiosity and clicks from their friends.

How: Use the pypresence library.

Feature: Show the Song Title, Artist, and "Time Remaining" in the user's Discord profile.

Ad Angle: "Show off your creations to your friends automatically."

2. "Prompt-to-Genre" Auto-Tagging
Effort: 🟡 Low (Regex/Text Parsing) Why: Suno libraries get messy fast. Users hate manually tagging 2,000 songs.

How: When downloading, scan the user's Prompt metadata. If the prompt contains words like "Synthwave," "Metal," or "Lofi," automatically write that to the Genre ID3 tag and a "Genre" column in your library.

Feature: "Smart Organize" button that categorizes their existing chaos.

Ad Angle: "Instantly organize your chaotic AI library by Genre."

3. Static Waveform Visualization
Effort: 🟡 Medium (UI drawing) Why: A flat list of files is boring. A waveform makes it look like a "Pro Audio Tool."

How: You don't need real-time animation (which is hard with VLC). Just generate a static waveform image of the song when it's selected. Use pydub or wave to read the file, analyze the peaks, and draw a cool-looking bar graph on a Canvas (CustomTkinter has canvas support).

Feature: Replace the empty space in the player bar with a sleek, generated waveform of the track.

Ad Angle: Screenshots look significantly more professional and technical.

4. "Export for Socials" (Simple Video Maker)
Effort: 🟡 Medium (Requires moviepy or ffmpeg) Why: 90% of your users want to post their songs to TikTok, YouTube Shorts, or Instagram. They currently have to open a video editor just to put the Album Art over the Audio.

How: Add an "Export Video" right-click option. It simply takes the Album Art (Image) + Song (Audio) and combines them into an .mp4 file.

Feature: One-click generation of a video file ready for upload.

Ad Angle: "Turn your audio into a YouTube video in one click."

5. Global Media Hotkeys
Effort: 🟢 Low Why: Users want to skip tracks while they are coding, gaming, or working in another window.

How: Use the keyboard or pynput library to listen for the standard media keys (Play/Pause, Next, Prev) on the keyboard, even when the app is minimized.

Feature: Control SunoSync from anywhere in Windows.

Ad Angle: "The seamless music player that stays out of your way."